In [44]:
#show featrue importance
import xgboost as xgb

def show_importances(features, importances):
    num = len(features)
    indices = np.argsort(importances)
    features_sorted = features[indices]
    importances_sorted = importances[indices]

    fig = plt.figure(figsize = (13,8))
    plt.title("Feature importances", fontsize = 16)
    rects = plt.barh(range(num), importances_sorted, 0.5)
    delta = np.max(importances) * 0.005
    for rect in rects:
            width = rect.get_width()
            plt.text(width + delta, rect.get_y() + rect.get_height()/2., '%.3f' % width, va='center', ha='left')

    plt.yticks(range(num), features_sorted)
    plt.ylabel("Feature", fontsize = 12)
    plt.xlabel("Feature importance", fontsize = 12)
    plt.show()

classifier = xgb.XGBClassifier()
classifier.fit(X, y)
show_importances(X.columns.values, classifier.feature_importances_)

In [50]:
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
from sklearn.metrics import make_scorer

#GridSearchCV
clf = xgb.XGBClassifier(n_estimators=1000)
max_depths = list(range(2,6))
learning_rates = [0.02, 0.04, 0.06, 0.08, 0.1]
param_grid = {'max_depth':max_depths, 'learning_rate':learning_rates}

grid_search = GridSearchCV(clf, param_grid, scoring=make_scorer(accuracy_score), cv=5, return_train_score=False)
grid_search = grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)
